not as good as 'vital signs' almost a carbon copy of it 's predecessor , 'vital signs ' . unlike 'vital signs ' , which was virtually flawless , this one has some flaws . this follow-up has less memorable songs , cheesier lyrics , and drags a little bit more . still , a good overall effort nonetheless . the highlight is obviously 'is this love ' , which reached as high as # 9 on the bilboard charts . overall , same mid-80 's power-ballad formula as 'vital signs ' , which is never a bad thing , is it